Key Match Events: Bradley Beal's performance as a sixth man ignited Phoenix back into the game
Phoenix outscored the 76ers, 36-27, in the third quarter
Devin Booker orchestrated the Phoenix offense with a team-high 10 assists
Philadelphia threatened to get back midway through the fourth but Durant scored back-to-back fade-away jumpers capped off by a reverse layup to balloon their cushion back to double digits
Miscellaneous Highlights: Joel Embiid missed the game due to a left foot sprain and a right sinus fracture
Others: Ryan Dunn was efficient in his start and knocked down a barrage of three-pointers and was also pesky on the defensive end as he took on the challenge of guarding Paul George in the game
